flowchart TD
    accTitle: AI to accessibility champion concept map
    accDescr {
        A concept map for Module 1. A single technical spine runs from
        Artificial Intelligence to Machine Learning to Deep Learning to
        Neural Networks to Large Language Models to Foundation Models to
        Generative AI. Generative AI produces accessibility drafts and
        explanations, which always pass through Human Review. Human Review
        branches into Accuracy, Privacy, Bias and Fairness, and Accessibility
        Expertise. GLOW workflows feed into Human Review and reach Campus
        Partners, who go on to become Accessibility Champions. The center of
        the map is human-centered accessibility capacity building, not the AI
        model.
    }
    AI[Artificial Intelligence] --> ML[Machine Learning]
    ML --> DL[Deep Learning]
    DL --> NN[Neural Networks]
    NN --> LLM[Large Language Models]
    LLM --> FM[Foundation Models]
    FM --> GenAI[Generative AI]
    GenAI --> Drafts[Accessibility Drafts and Explanations]
    Drafts --> HumanReview[Human Review]
    HumanReview --> Accuracy[Accuracy]
    HumanReview --> Privacy[Privacy]
    HumanReview --> Bias[Bias and Fairness]
    HumanReview --> Access[Accessibility Expertise]
    GLOW[GLOW Workflows] --> HumanReview
    GLOW --> Partners[Campus Partners]
    Partners --> Champions[Accessibility Champions]
